WEBVTT



00:00:09.952 --> 00:00:13.248
Welcome to the Canopy Roads Baptist Church podcast.

00:00:13.376 --> 00:00:17.472
Our mission is to develop fully devoted followers of Christ.

00:00:17.888 --> 00:00:27.744
Our church is on a journey through the entire book of Psalms, where we are reading and reflecting on one Psalm every day. On today's episode, we're excited to have Sophie Dangerfield reading Psalm one forty nine.

00:00:30.432 --> 00:00:35.968
Praise the Lord! Sing to the Lord a new song, His praise in the assembly of the godly.

00:00:35.808 --> 00:00:40.736
Let Israel be glad in his Maker, Let the children of Zion rejoice in their King.

00:00:40.736 --> 00:00:46.048
Let them praise his name with dancing, making melody to him with tambourine and lyre.

00:00:46.368 --> 00:00:51.488
For the Lord takes pleasure in his people. He adorns the humble with salvation.

00:00:51.328 --> 00:00:55.584
Let the godly insult and glory let them sing for joy on their beds

00:00:55.680 --> 00:01:00.448
But the high praises of God be in their throats, and to its swords in their hands.

00:01:00.224 --> 00:01:10.272
To execute vengeance on the nations and punishments on the people, to bind their kings with chains and their nobles with fetters of iron, to execute on them judgment writ.

00:01:09.792 --> 00:01:10.752
written.

00:01:10.784 --> 00:01:14.688
This is honor for all his godly ones. Praise the Lord.

00:01:16.704 --> 00:01:19.456
That was Psalms 149.

00:01:19.648 --> 00:01:27.776
So, in your church's worship, can you picture God joining in with the right and spontaneity, or nodding off in boredom? How about you?

00:01:27.712 --> 00:01:30.656
What kind of celebration does God delight in?

00:01:38.880 --> 00:01:47.040
We hope this message was encouraging to you. If you would like this kind of content delivered directly to you, consider subscribing to our channel.

00:01:47.104 --> 00:01:56.544
If you'd like more information about our church, please visit us on the web at canopyroads.org. And thanks for listening to the Canopy Roads Baptist Church podcast.
